product_name: IT CosmeticsConfidence in a Cream Barrier Boost Skin Barrier Repair Daily Moisturizer
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganGive BackIT Cosmetics Confidence in a Cream® Barrier Boost Skin Barrier Repair Daily Moisturizer is an ultra-gentle, fragrance-free barrier cream that delivers 100HR hydration to strengthen & soothe even the most sensitive skin. This lightweight moisturizer can be applied AM & PM for bouncy, recovered skin.
details: DetailsBenefitsAfter 1 use: Clinically smoother, softer, more radiant skin*After 3 days: Visible improvement in dry fine lines, dry spots, elasticity*95% agree it wears well under makeup**Ultra-gentle, lightweight & fragrance-free moisturizerDermatologist-Tested for safetySafe to use on sensitive & sensitized skinAccepted by the National Eczema AssociationSafe for use after retinol^ & lasers^^*Results based on an 8-week clinical study.**Results based on an 8-week consumer study.^Safety tested with IT Cosmetics Hello Results Retinol Serum-in-Cream.^^Non-ablative laser.Research Results+94% Clinical improvement in skin smoothness, softness and radiance+75% Clinical improvement in texture smoothness+68% Clinical improvement in visible dry spots-30% Clinical reduction in visible rednessResults based on an 8-week clinical study.Key IngredientsFormulated With:1% Vitamin F Complex: Helps to hydrate & replenish skin barrier; vitamin F is an essential part of skin's natural ceramide productionCeramide: Helps seal in moisture to support skin's natural barrier functionItem 2633016How To UseOn Bare Skin: Use liberally, applying to clean skin from face to chest every AM & PM.Under Makeup: Plays well with CC+ Cream and your favorite complexion products. Apply with IT Brushes for ULTA Airbrush Dual-Ended Flawless Complexion Concealer & Foundation Brush #132.IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Glycerin, Ethyl Oleate, Butyrospermum Parkii Butter / Shea Butter, Glyceryl Stearate Citrate, Niacinamide, Behenyl Alcohol, Squalane, Lauryl Laurate, C12-16 Alcohols, Ammonium Polyacryloyldimethyl Taurate, Dimethicone, Linoleic Acid, Panthenol, Phenoxyethanol, Palmitic Acid, Hydrogenated Lecithin, Caprylyl Glycol, Ectoin, Oleic Acid, Tocopherol, Centella Asiatica Extract, Xanthan Gum, Phytic Acid, Ceramide Np, Adenosine, Sodium Hydroxide, Stearic Acid, Colloidal Oatmeal, Hydroxypalmitoyl Sphinganine, Linolenic Acid, Citric Acid, Acetyl Dipeptide-1 Cetyl Ester.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: On Bare Skin: Use liberally, applying to clean skin from face to chest every AM & PM.Under Makeup: Plays well with CC+ Cream and your favorite complexion products. Apply with IT Brushes for ULTA Airbrush Dual-Ended Flawless Complexion Concealer & Foundation Brush #132.

reviews.headline: Definitely for dry skin!
reviews.comments: Purchased this to switch it up from the Confidence (yellow jar). At first I really liked it, but after 1 week or so, it started to feel very greasy on my skin & my skin felt very weighed down. I was noticeably oily during the day. I would barely feel my face and have oil/grease all over my hand. Would work well with someone that has very dry skin, but if you have oily skin, I would avoid this!

reviews.headline: 10/5 stars
reviews.comments: I have tried so many moisturizers for my dry skin from CeraVe to Biologique Recherche and nothing has worked like this. My skin is glowier, bouncier, and doesn't just sit on top of my skin. HIGHLY recommend.

reviews.headline: Smooth and creamy
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Such a creamy texture. Nice and smooth. Has a very light scent that is pretty pleasant not strong at all. Definitely makes my face feel super moisturized and plumper. Seriously feels like confidence in a jar.

reviews.headline: Oh. My. Gosh.
reviews.comments: I have been using this product for almost 2 weeks.. My skin looks the best it has in years and im 26. This has slightly minimized my pores, really hydrated my skin, improved my makeup texture… I know this product doesnt claim to help with acne but when i tell you that I had inflamed acne on my chin and along my jaw line for the last couple years and this product has made it almost nonexistent… Girl just get it. It's worth the money.

reviews.headline: Amazing moisturizer!
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review.  I absolutely love this moisturizer and will be buying more when I run out!   My skin feels hydrated and plumped up.   It leaves a nice, healthy glow.  It also wears well under makeup.

reviews.headline: Wonderful Moisturizer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really have enjoyed using the IT Cosmetics Confidence in a Cream Barrier Boost Moisturizer.  There is no scent and it has a light and smooth creamy texture.  It gives the skin a nice glow.  This product will continue to be in my skincare routine.

reviews.headline: Fantastic Cream!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This cream is fantastic! It addresses all the concerns associated with a damaged skin barrier, including dryness, sensitivity, uneven skin tone, uneven texture, and facial redness. I love how hydrating it is; my skin feels bouncy and plump after each use, giving me a natural glow. My skin particularly appreciates it during the colder months, as it effectively alleviates my dry patches.

reviews.headline: It Cosmetics got it right!
reviews.comments: I received It Cosmetics Boost Skin Repair Moisturizer in exchange for an honest review. As I have gotten older, I've noticed the change in my skin. I have had to try many products to get my skin back on track. I'm very excited that It Cosmetics got it right. A little goes a long way. It has a great consistency and glides effortlessly. It isn't heavy and really helps my skin retain the moisture. I definitely recommend this moisturizer as a staple in your daily skin care regime.

reviews.headline: My favorite Moisturizer
reviews.comments: I am so pleased with this Weightless Daily Repair Moisturizer by It Cosmetics. It goes on so smooth and is not greasy at all. Feels like it leaves a matte finish. I typically get oily skin throughout the day and this thankfully does not add to that. I actually feel like it helps keep me less oily. It's suitable for sensitive skin and is formulated without fragrances, which I love. This has become my favorite moisturizer since trying.

reviews.headline: An amazing thick barrier cream!
reviews.comments:
IT Cosmetics Confidence cream is thick and protects your skin from everyday damage, air, toxins and more. 

This cream is super hydrating and feels great on the skin. I think my favorite thing about this cream, is that it doesn't soak in super quick like many of them! For extra benefits, add serums to the cream before using! 

I definitely recommend BUT, I am not sure it's worth the price or not yet….

I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Lightweight in feel, heavy healing!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Light, but moisturizing and gentle on the skin, perfect for skin barrier renewal during the warmer months of the year!  A really nice, smooth and easily spreadable texture.  It is easily absorbed into the skin to heal and repair!

reviews.headline: Beauty must have
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Excellent face cream! This has no scent, & is a thick, white, lotiony cream. It works well under my makeup, & I like the moisture it is giving my dry face! I am using this as a day cream, over my serum, & under my sunscreen & makeup. The packaging is super cute & it's a great quality option.

reviews.headline: I would definitely purchase this product!!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This skin barrier moisturizer is unlike any other! It leaves my skin feeling ultra smooth, hydrated, and bouncy! Nice scent and packaging is nice as well! Great product all around!!

reviews.headline: Nice
reviews.comments: This confidence and cream barrier boost is not very thick and consistency, and it has really no sense to it, which is fine with me. It doesn't have to be. I said to cosmic well quick and easy skin glow after.

reviews.headline: Love This Moisturizer
reviews.comments: I Would Definitely Purchase. It Really Helped My Skin Get Back To Normal When My Skin Started Getting Too Dry With The Cold Winter Weather. It Went On Smooth, And Absorbed Nicely Leaving My Skin Feeling Hydrated. It Also Has No Scent.

reviews.headline: My skin new best friend
reviews.comments: I've been using IT Cosmetics Confidence in a Cream Barrier Boost for a few weeks now, and I'm seriously impressed. The texture is rich but not heavy, and it absorbs quickly into the skin without leaving any greasy feeling. My skin tends to get dry and a bit sensitive, especially during colder months, but this moisturizer has really helped calm things down and keep my skin feeling soft and hydrated all day.

reviews.headline: must have moisturizer
reviews.comments: I've been using the moisturizer for a few weeks now, and honestly, it's a keeper. The ingredient list is impressive. The texture is super creamy without being heavy. The scent is present but not overwhelming. For those sensitive to smells, it shouldn't be a dealbreaker. As for effectiveness, I noticed a real difference in how calm and hydrated my skin felt after just a few days. It especially helps during colder months when my skin tends to feel tight or irritated. All in all, this moisturizer delivers on what it promises.

reviews.headline: Love the price point......
reviews.comments: I love the feel of this face cream. It's moisturizing  wiyhout a heavy greasy feel (oily tzone) or build up on my pores. It actually reminds me of the Tatcha face. Great quality without the hefty price tag. I would purchase again .....

reviews.headline: It's a Keeper for me!
reviews.comments: I recently tried out the new product and Loved the way my skin felt and appeared after use. After 1 use, I could see my skin was more radiant and soft. t dries quickly without leaving an oily texture afterward. My skin feels hydrated and fresh. The packaging is beautiful and in an easy-to-open jar. Fragrance-free. The main ingredient is water with antioxidants.

reviews.headline: Great for dry sensitive skin
reviews.comments:
This cream is good for dryer, sensitive skin. It goes on silky but may be a little greasy for oily skin. You can see how it helps irritated skin. It is also unscented which is a must.
I received this product at no cost in exchange for my honest review

media.headline: Great moisturizer for sensitive skin
media.caption: IT Cosmetics Confidence in a Cream Barrier Boost

faceoff_positive.comments:
As a beauty enthusiast with dry, dehydrated skin, I was excited to try the Confidence in a Cream Barrier Boost Skin Barrier Repair Daily Moisturizer from IT Cosmetics. I received this product #Complimentary in exchange for my honest feedback. All opinions are my own.
First Impressions & Packaging
The moisturizer comes in a sleek, beautiful glass jar that gives it a clean, luxurious look. I promptly incorporated it into my skincare routine, replacing my usual lotion to see how it performed.
Texture & Application
Upon application, my skin immediately felt soothed and relieved from its usual tightness. The cream is completely fragrance-free, which I appreciate. It has a white color and a smooth, whipped consistency that feels lightweight yet nourishing. It absorbs easily into the skin without pilling or leaving a sticky residue. I love how well it layers with my nighttime skincare routine and how seamlessly it sits under foundation during the day.
Ingredients & Benefits
This newest release from IT Cosmetics is dermatologist-tested, safe for sensitive skin, and accepted by the National Eczema Association—making it a great option for those with skin concerns. Due to its gentle formulation, it's safe to use on sensitized skin after retinol, laser treatments, or other post-procedure care.
Key ingredients include:
Vitamin F Complex – Hydrates dry skin and helps replenish the skin barrier.
Ceramides – Seal in moisture to strengthen the skin's natural protective barrier.
Additional benefits include:
✔ Reduction in the appearance of fine lines and dry patches
✔ Improved skin elasticity
✔ A more radiant, healthy-looking complexion over time
Final Thoughts
After using this cream for a couple of weeks, I've noticed my skin feels smoother, more hydrated, and has an overall improved appearance. It has officially become a must-have in my skincare routine! If you have dry, dehydrated skin or need a barrier-repair moisturizer, I highly recommend the Confidence in a Cream Barrier Boost Skin Barrier Repair Daily Moisturizer from IT Cosmetics.
faceoff_positive.headline: A New Must Have!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I added this moisturizer to my regular skin routine for one week. I used it once daily for a total of 7 days. My initial impression was that I like the packaging is beautiful and I liked the light consistency of the cream. I also liked how there was no detectable fragrance and it quickly sank into my skin. However, the next morning, I looked at my face and saw little whiteheads in areas I typically do not break out, like my eyebrows, upper lip and nose. While I do have mild acne, my usual breakouts tends to be either closed comedones or cystic spots. I rarely, if ever, get random tiny whiteheads grouped in places. 

Despite that, I continued to use it for the full week to give it a fair chance, but my skin got progressively more irritated, so I had to stop using it. 

Not wanting to waste product, I decided to test it as a hand cream instead. The weather where I live is currently cold, so my hands are naturally dryer. Again, the cream quickly absorbed after I rubbed it into my hands, which I thought was great. There was no greasiness or stickiness. Sadly, after an hour, my hands were back to dry. I was actually pretty surprised by that. 

Overall, I am pretty bummed that this one did not work for me. If you do decide to try this out make sure you are looking for a light moisturizer and you aren't sensitive to any of the ingredients.
faceoff_negative.headline: Did not work well with my skin.
